      "content": "right, \"speculative science\"... but the way it responds to my thoughts makes me think the \"evidence\" is just being hidden or is too subtle for standard telescopes to pick up. if an advanced civilization wanted to monitor a whole planet without being obvious, using the natural light of a huge constellation like Orion as a carrier wave for a signal would be the perfect way to hide in plain sight, wouldn't it? it would look like just natural stellar activity to anyone not looking for the pattern. how would someone even begin to detect a signal that's disguised as natural astronomical phenomena?",
